name: I ate myself in an emergency
description:
is a small interpellation that became the invisible core of my silent symphony.
    It depicts only those mysterious interactions that harmonize form and tone through a hidden but unobtrusive scene.
     A scene that no disturbance or change can stop or delay.
     The space is the highest.
     It is as if an ethereal wave is sweeping over the surfaces
     And the visible manifestations absorb them to shape and shape them.
     And then spread them like a fragrant perfume
     Like a reflection of themselves
     Like an imperceptible dust that covers all the surrounding surfaces.
